Establishing Baseline & Attribution

  To prove SelfPM's impact (not just user outcomes), I need to establish a baseline during Week 1 of observation. This allows me to say: "Seekers improved
  target completion by X% from their Week 1 baseline after Y weeks on SelfPM." Without baseline, I can't attribute improvement to the product.

  Engagement Metrics

  Beyond outcome metrics, I'll track:
  - Session frequency (how often seekers return daily/weekly)
  - Missed entries - distinguishing between "didn't log on at all" (engagement problem) vs. "skipped specific ores" (friction/avoidance on that ore) —
  different problems requiring different interventions
  - Note character count (baseline at Week 1, track increase over time — more notes = more awareness = more insight potential)
  - Creation of new ores (shows active observation and learning)

  The Funnel

  Join
    ↓
  Complete Week 1 (baseline established)
    ↓
  Complete Week 2 (first CPO report)
    ↓
  Graduate Observation (85%+ causal relationship between enablers and target)
    ↓
  Complete First Sprint Week
    ↓
  Pass Sprint (3 weeks, with at least 1 week achieving target goal)

  Each stage has a conversion rate to track. Drop-off at each stage tells me where product friction exists.

  Causal Relationship Calculation

  Causal relationship score = (days target met when enablers completed) / (total days enablers completed). Threshold for graduation: ≥0.85